snippet.textDisplay: Whenever I point finger guns at my puppy, she gets down and barks at me. Then she jumps around all excited, paws a few times at my hand and then tries to eat the gun. I have no idea where she learned that guns are bad. We got her when she was 2 months old, and we've never taught her "bang" (until we realized she reacted to them. In Sadie's case, it isn't a 'play dead' thing it's a 'I have a gun so you should pay attention to me' thing. So whenever we use finger guns and say "bang" she turns around and sits. Or fights back. It depends on her mood.

snippet.textDisplay: Not-so-fun fact: anxious dogs often don't want to lie down because that puts them in a vulnerable position which is scary for them. Making them do it is a great way to make your dog hate "down"... and training in general. Pushing a dog  onto their side is not "teaching" them, and anyone with basic knowledge of dog body language can see that both dogs are confused and stressed throughout the video.
